api.body:
require "pixcHelper"
require "pixcDriver"
self.pixcHelper = createPixcHelper(pixc,self())
self.driver = createPixcDriver()

self.driver:setLogFunction(function (...) pixc.log(...) end)
self.driver:setConnectionLifecycleCallback(self.pixcHelper.wrapCallback(self().IsConnected))
self.Internal.setRecFunction()
self.driver:createParser()

self.universe = self.pixcHelper:getProperty("Universe","1")
self.recMode = self.pixcHelper:getProperty("Receive Mode","Multicast")
self.adapter = pixc.getRoot().Utils.Network.convertLocalAdapterEntry(self.pixcHelper:getProperty("Local Adapter","Any"))
self.portRec = tonumber(self.pixcHelper:getProperty("Port Receive","5568"))
self.filter = self.pixcHelper.toBool(self.pixcHelper:getProperty("Filter Priority","false"))
self.priority = tonumber(self.pixcHelper:getProperty("Priority",100))

self.universeUp = math.floor(tonumber(self.universe/256))
self.universeDown = math.floor(tonumber(self.universe-(256*self.universeUp)))

if self.recMode == "Multicast" then

	self.ip = "239.255." .. self.universeUp .. "." .. self.universeDown
	pixc.log("Multicast IP:" .. self.ip)
	self.driver:enableBroadcast();
	self.driver:joinMulticast(self.ip)
end

self.driver:set("udp","0.0.0.0",0,self.adapter,self.portRec,nil);
self.driver:connect();
api.name: init

api.body:
self._connectionLifecycle = pixcCommon.execAttribute(false, self._connectionLifecycle, val, doSet)
return self._connectionLifecycle
api.name: IsConnected

api.body:
self._recName = pixcCommon.execAttribute(0, self._recName, val, doSet)

return self._recName
api.name: recName

api.body:
if self.driver ~= nil then
self.driver:close()
end
self.driver = nil
api.name: uninit

elems.body:
self.driver:overrrideReceiveCallbackFunction(
function (data)
local bytes = { string.byte(data, 1,-1) }

local header = {
	0x00,0x10, --Preamble Size
	0x00,0x00, --Post-amble Size
	0x41,0x53,0x43,0x2d,0x45,0x31,0x2e,0x31,0x37,0x00,0x00,0x00 --ACN Packet Identifier
}

--local channelCount = bytes[125] + (256*bytes[124])
--pixc.log("channelcount:",channelCount)

for _ in pairs(header) do --chekc header
	if bytes[_] ~= header[_] then
		pixc.log("header not match",header[_],bytes[_],_)
		return
	end
end
pixc.log(bytes[113],self.seq,bytes[125],bytes[126],bytes[127])

--filter priority
if self.filter == true and self.priority ~= bytes[109] then
	return
end

--check universe
if bytes[114] ~= self.universeUp or bytes[115] ~= self.universeDown then 
	return
end

--after init return first receive value if selfseq == nil
if self.seq == nil then
	self.seq = bytes[112]
	return
end

--check seq number
if self.seq + 1 ~= bytes[112] then
	if self.seq == 255 and bytes[112] == 0 then
		self.seq = 0
	else
		self.seq = bytes[112]
		return	
	end
end
self.seq = bytes[112]


--USITT Standard Start Code needs to be 0
if bytes[126] ~= 0 then
	return
end

local name = "" 
for i = 45, 108 do
	if bytes[i] ~= 0 then
		name = name .. string.char(bytes[i])
	end
end

if name ~= self._recName then
	self.recName(name,true)
end

for i = 127,#bytes do
	local num = i - 126
	if self['_Channel' .. num] ~= bytes[i] then
		self.Channels["Channel" .. num](bytes[i],true)
	end
end

end, true)
elems.name: setRecFunction

elems.body: return {"Multicast","Unicast"}
